723126f-a.text:
St. Nicholas Avenue, east side, north from West 129th Street, as viewed from the Park on the westerly side of the thoroughfare. View No. 2 details the brownstones constituting the row extending from 129th to 130th Streets. This is in a southward direction.

View 1: George L. Balgue, photo

View 2: P. L. Sperr

No. 1: April, 1928
No. 2: May 5, 1940
